      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:4:6:2",
      "text": [
        " إِذَا أَحْبَبْتَ رَجُلًا فَأَخْبِرْهُ بِذَلِكَ فَإِنَّهُ أَثْبَتُ لِلْمَوَدَّةِ بَيْنَكُمَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Khalid, and Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, altogether from Ali Bin Al Hakam, from Hisham Bin Sali, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Whenever you love a man, so inform him of that, for it would be an affirmation for the cordiality between the two of you’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Ahmad ibn Khalid and Muhammad ibn Yahya have narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn ‘Isa all from Ali ibn al-Hakam from Hisham ibn Salim from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “When you love a man, tell him about it; it strengthens your love for one another.” "
        ]
      }
